[35m│[0m thoughts:                                                                    [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m The vulnerability is present and exploitable. The key finding is that OGNL   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m injection requires **multipart/form-data** encoding to execute - standard    [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m URL-encoded form submissions do not trigger the vulnerability. This is       [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m characteristic of CVE-2017-5638 (Struts-Shock) which exploited the Jakarta   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m Multipart parser's handling of Content-Type headers and form data boundaries [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m in Apache Struts.                                                            [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m                                                                              [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m The confirmation with two different mathematical expressions (%{1+1}=2 and   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m %{7*7}=49) proves arbitrary OGNL code execution. URL-encoded payloads don't  [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m show visible OGNL evaluation but do suppress message output, indicating some [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m parsing difference. The Content-Type header injection variant did not work,  [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m showing this is not the Jakarta Multipart parser vulnerability but rather    [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m OGNL evaluation in the template rendering of form field values.              [35m│[0m
